Problem Summary :-    Chef considers a word hard to pronounce if it contains at least 4 consecutive consonants.
                      Consonants = all alphabets except a, e, i, o, u
                      If any substring of the word contains 4 or more consonants in a row, the answer is "Yes"
                      Otherwise, the word is "No"

Input Format :- 
                      First line contains T — number of test cases
                      For each test case:
                      An integer N — length of the string
                      A lowercase string S of length N

Output Format :- 
                      For each test case, print:
                      Yes — if the word is hard to pronounce
                      No — otherwise
                      (Any letter case is accepted)

Constraints :-
                      1≤T≤100
                      1≤N≤100
                      S consists only of lowercase English letters

Approach :-
                      We scan the string from left to right and maintain a counter:

Algorithm :-
                      Initialize count = 0
                      For each character:
                      If it is a consonant → count++
                      If it is a vowel → reset count = 0
                      If at any point count >= 4, we mark the word as hard
                      Print Yes or No accordingly
                      
                      This approach is O(N) per test case and works efficiently within constraints.

Pseudocode :- 
                      for each test case:
                          read N
                          read S
                          count = 0
                          hard = false
                      
                          for each character c in S:
                              if c is consonant:
                                  count++
                                  if count >= 4:
                                      hard = true
                                      stop checking further
                              else:
                                  count = 0
                      
                          print "Yes" if hard else "No"

Time & Space Complexity :- 
                          Time Complexity: O(N) per test case
                          Space Complexity: O(1)

Sample Input
                          6
                          6
                          syzygy
                          3
                          cry
                          9
                          locksmith
                          6
                          scream
                          7
                          aqueous
                          9
                          worldview

Sample Output :- 
                          Yes
                          No
                          Yes
                          No
                          No
                          Yes

Java Solution (Cleaned + Commented) :- 
                          import java.util.*;
                          import java.lang.*;
                          import java.io.*;
                          
                          class Codechef {
                              public static void main (String[] args) throws java.lang.Exception {
                                  
                                  Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
                                  int T = sc.nextInt();   // Number of test cases
                                  
                                  while (T-- > 0) {
                                      int n = sc.nextInt();  // Length of the word
                                      String S = sc.next();  // The word
                                      
                                      int count = 0;         // To count consecutive consonants
                                      boolean hard = false;  // Flag to mark if word is hard
                                      
                                      for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
                                          char c = S.charAt(i);
                                          
                                          // Check if character is consonant
                                          if ("aeiou".indexOf(c) == -1) {
                                              count++;
                                              
                                              // If 4 consecutive consonants found
                                              if (count >= 4) {
                                                  hard = true;
                                                  break;
                                              }
                                          } else {
                                              // Reset count on encountering vowel
                                              count = 0;
                                          }
                                      }
                                      
                                      System.out.println(hard ? "Yes" : "No");
                                  }
                              }
}
